  "description": "A preface, please: I know that \u0026ldquo;post-modern\u0026rdquo; is often used as a dogwhistle to refer to Jewish culture. I promise I don\u0026rsquo;t mean it in that sense. As you read the text, I hope you appreciate the irony that I\u0026rsquo;m asking you to, on this small matter, take me at my word.\nA lot of people don\u0026rsquo;t realize that they don\u0026rsquo;t believe anything. This is, in contemporary society, if not inherently, significantly more of a problem among the post-modern conservative members of my society, so that\u0026rsquo;s where this critique will focus. However, it seems to apply to some extent to nearly everyone who is a post-modernist or unknowing adherrent to such an ideology, so if you don\u0026rsquo;t identify as a conservative or moderate, don\u0026rsquo;t necessarily assume this text isn\u0026rsquo;t going to criticize you as well.\n",
